import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['precipitation'] = pd.to_numeric(data['precipitation'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='precipitation', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['precipitation'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['precipitation'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date'])
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_max', data=data, label='Max Temperature')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_min', data=data, label='Min Temperature')
    plt.title('How does temperature vary over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
